    <item>
      <title>How To Change VSCode Theme By Time of Day</title>
      <link>/posts/how-to-change-your-vscode-theme-depending-on-the-time-of-day/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 28 Jun 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>/posts/how-to-change-your-vscode-theme-depending-on-the-time-of-day/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Eye comfort is very important, especially to programmers, who spend most of their day looking at code in their favorite editor.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;ve already mentioned a few &lt;a href=&#34;https://valticus.pro/tags/theme/&#34;&gt;themes&lt;/a&gt; I like, and today I am going to teach you how to set your editor up in such away that the theme changes automatically depending on what time of day it is.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Take a look at the three screenshots above:&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;/images/theme-afternoon.webp&#34;&#xA;    alt=&#34;Cobalt2&#34; width=&#34;75%&#34; height=&#34;75%&#34;&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;&#xA;      &lt;h4&gt;Cobalt2&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;/images/theme-morning.webp&#34;&#xA;    alt=&#34;Night Owl Light&#34; width=&#34;75%&#34; height=&#34;75%&#34;&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;&#xA;      &lt;h4&gt;Night Owl Light&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;/images/theme-night.webp&#34;&#xA;    alt=&#34;Night Owl&#34; width=&#34;75%&#34; height=&#34;75%&#34;&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;&#xA;      &lt;h4&gt;Night Owl&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>How To Change Your GitHub Theme</title>
      <link>/posts/how-to-change-your-github-theme/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 04 Apr 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>/posts/how-to-change-your-github-theme/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;So, as you may or may not know, &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/&#34;&gt;GitHub&lt;/a&gt; is testing themes for its website, and the feature is now in beta according to &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.github.com/en/github/setting-up-and-managing-your-github-user-account/managing-your-theme-settings&#34;&gt;GitHub Docs&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;To change how your &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/&#34;&gt;GitHub&lt;/a&gt; looks, you need to log in to your &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/&#34;&gt;GitHub&lt;/a&gt; account, click your profile pictures, choose &lt;em&gt;Settings&lt;/em&gt; &amp;gt; &lt;em&gt;Appearance&lt;/em&gt; and on the section that opens, choose one of the three themes that are currently available.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Below are the screen shots, courtesy of &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.github.com/en/github/setting-up-and-managing-your-github-user-account/managing-your-theme-settings&#34;&gt;GitHub Docs&lt;/a&gt;:&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;/images/github-theme-userbar-account-settings.webp&#34;&#xA;    alt=&#34;GitHub Account Settings&#34; width=&#34;75%&#34; height=&#34;75%&#34;&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;&#xA;      &lt;h4&gt;GitHub Account Settings&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;/images/github-theme-appearance-tab.webp&#34;&#xA;    alt=&#34;GitHub Appearance&#34; width=&#34;75%&#34; height=&#34;75%&#34;&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;&#xA;      &lt;h4&gt;GitHub Appearance&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;/images/github-theme-theme-settings-radio-buttons.webp&#34;&#xA;    alt=&#34;GitHub Themes&#34; width=&#34;75%&#34; height=&#34;75%&#34;&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;&#xA;      &lt;h4&gt;GitHub Themes&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
